WRITING.TEXT: Im at a crossroads of which car to sell. I currently have three vehicals: a 2001 Isuzu rodeo lifted (108,000 mi paid off), a 2012 Jeep Grand Cherokee (55,000 mi owe 10k, 380 per month, 3 yr @ 2.9%), and now a work truck that I drive mon-fri. Backstory, my transmission went out in the rodeo back in September. It's an older car so at the time I decided to invest in a newer more reliable car, and was financially stable to do so. I found a 2012 Jeep through a friend for a great deal of $14k (with the options, kbb had the value at 17k). I bought the Jeep, and tried to sell my rodeo with a broken transmission, but was unsuccessful. Fast forward a couple months and I get promoted and am given a company truck that I use mon-frday. I might drive my Jeep 50 miles on the weekend at most. I have recently fixed the rodeo with intentions to sell it. Since I barley use my personal vehical, should I sell my Jeep or Rodeo? I could use the extra cash to help pay off student loans or save/401k/invest or keep the Jeep and have a more reliable vehical and build credit with payments. Thanks for reading and any advice give. If you need more details, let me know. I apologise for any format or grammatical errors in advance.
